column5: While spending a few days up in the Haliburton's fishing for Rainbow and Brook trout I stopped by a couple of small rivers and was able to see first hand some really nice Walleye heading up the rivers for the spring spawning ritual.  Here is one of many pictures I took.... this one is cool as it shows both a male and female Walleye beside each other!  You just got to love the spring time!    The trout fishing was great also.... here is a couple of beauti Rainbow's taken while trolling a spinner and woolly bugger combo.    Take care and good Fish'n.... Greg.
Those rainbows look yummy, nice report and cool pics.
The first one's a great pic Greg.    Second one is fine too. Thanks for sharing.
that one must be a city trout...got some crazy piercing through his nose
does anyone not see the picture of the pope in there? i swear it it's right there in the first pic, my wife says i'm delusional... maybe i do need a head check :s
Nice shots, Greg. Thanks for sharing.
NICE RAINBOWS..  ...well done greg,they look amazing,and thanks for sharing the walleye spawning pics,its great to know that they are doing their part,successfully,cheers
You might have had a little too much holy water today, Bud.
thats a great picture!
Now thats funny there,I dont care who you are. Joe
Puff Puff Pass  BEAUTY Pictures Greg!
Those rainbows look like they are in the bottom of a Sportspal canoe. Am I right? Nice walleye pics too by the way.

You see the pope too?  That's great, I thought I was nuts.  That's a huge relief right there.  On the other hand, I'm a very, very lucky guy and fortunate too.  This is all because my wife pretty much sorta sees the pope in the photo also.  You gotta count your blessings.
I spy another eye. Can you find it?  >Bill
awesome pics, the 3rd is is to the right of the big walleyes tail

I see 4 walleyes in the picture, one large female, a smaller (male) beside it, a smaller (male?) about 50% covered by the female's tale, and a fourth with it's head just poking through the top middle of the picture with it's right eye reflecting light.  Cool pics Greg, thanks for the post, makes me wish I was out fishing instead of working.  Stan
Very nice pics! Thanks for sharing! Wish I can go fishing now.
Those are funny look,n hooks there Greg.LOL  Nice shot of the eyes.  Thanks for sharing.
the pope I thought it was Bin Laden

Stan..... you win the prize buddy!!  You are correct as there are in fact 4 Walleye in the pic....... I think you are in the wrong business..... should be 'Seeing specialist' vs 'Hearing Specialist'.... LOLO...  Take care and see you on the water.... Greg.
cool pics!  Thanks for sharing!  Cheers!
